<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="87" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1633,2018]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,2013]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="87" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1633,1658]" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Karsch)" authorityName="Savaris &amp; Marinoni &amp; Mathis" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Savaris &amp; Marinoni &amp; Mathis" baseAuthorityYear="2016" box="[594,898,1633,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Peltopsilopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anisotomoides">
<emphasis box="[594,787,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">P. anisotomoides</emphasis>
(Karsch)
</taxonomicName>
but differs as follows: Body generally shiny, polished, navy blue to dark brown; moderately small shore flies, body length 
<quantity box="[1042,1144,1670,1694]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.20 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[1161,1272,1669,1694]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ‒ 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1768,1791]" captionTargetBox="[152,1426,463,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,447,1747]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 ‒ 6. Adult of Peltopsilopa Hendel. (1 ‒ 3) P. acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (1) Head, frontal view. (2) Body, dorsal view. (3) Same, lateral view. (4 ‒ 6) P. anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). (4) Head, frontal view. (5) Body, dorsal view. (6) Same, lateral view. (7 ‒ 9) P. schwarzi Cresson (Cuba. Cienfuegos: Cayamas (22 ° 14 ' N, 80 ° 48 ' W; 26 m )). (7) Head, frontal view. (8) Body, dorsal view. (9) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054068/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Figs. 2‒3</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[1293,1363,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Head:</emphasis>
Frons shiny, polished with metallic luster; ocelli arranged in isosceles triangle, distance between posterior ocelli greater than between either posterior ocellus and anteromedial ocellus; vertex acutely angled, creased. Antenna yellow; dorsum of basal flagellomere tan to brownish yellow; arista with 8‒9 dorsal rays. Face shallowly arched, shiny, polished, similar to frons, bearing an inclinate seta at lateral margin at midheight; facial ratio 0.63; ventral facial emargination conspicuously arched. Gena-to-eye ratio 0.19. Maxillary palpus irregularly spatulate, blackish brown (
<figureCitation box="[159,225,1885,1910]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 ‒ 6" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1768,1791]" captionTargetBox="[152,1426,463,1744]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,447,1747]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 1 ‒ 6. Adult of Peltopsilopa Hendel. (1 ‒ 3) P. acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (1) Head, frontal view. (2) Body, dorsal view. (3) Same, lateral view. (4 ‒ 6) P. anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). (4) Head, frontal view. (5) Body, dorsal view. (6) Same, lateral view. (7 ‒ 9) P. schwarzi Cresson (Cuba. Cienfuegos: Cayamas (22 ° 14 ' N, 80 ° 48 ' W; 26 m )). (7) Head, frontal view. (8) Body, dorsal view. (9) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054068/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[250,340,1885,1910]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="86">Thorax:</emphasis>
Almost entirely deep blue to brownish blue, shiny, microsculptured. Mesonotal length 
<quantity box="[1328,1432,1885,1910]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="1.95">1.95 mm</quantity>
; acrostichal setae in 2 regular rows on each side, presutural pair slightly enlarged, displaced laterally; scutum deep, navy blue, polished, shiny; scutellum greatly enlarged, longer than scutum, shiny, microsculptured, appearing shallowly and slightly wrinkled, scutellar length 
<quantity box="[707,810,1993,2018]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" pageId="3" pageNumber="86" unit="mm" value="1.45">1.45 mm</quantity>
, almost as wide as long, scutellar length-to-width ratio 0.88, shape in lateral view shallowly dome-like, posterior margin bluntly rounded with corners broadly rounded, with basal and apical setae, these small, with a few addition setulae laterally and on dorsal surface, but these not conspicuous, ventral scutellar surface shallowly concave; scutellar base lacking a dentate, sharp, short projection laterally; anepisternum with few small light setulae, except for 2 thicker black setae on posterior margin; katepisternum with a strong dorsal seta. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[703,788,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 45 ‒ 46" captionStartId="12.[151,264,514,537]" captionTargetBox="[161,1411,187,488]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,179,494]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 45 ‒ 46. Wings. (45) Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Costa Rica. Intercepted in Los Angeles Airport). (46) Peltopsilopa anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054080/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
) mostly hyaline, faintly infuscate, tannish, basal fourth, including crossvein r-m, darkened; length 
<quantity box="[641,748,332,357]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="4" pageNumber="87" unit="mm" value="1.95">1.95 mm</quantity>
; costal vein ratio 0.86; M vein ratio 1.03. Femora blackish brown except for yellowish apices; tibiae yellow, slightly brownish yellow medially; basitarsomere of foreleg brownish medially, apices yellow, tarsi of mid- and hindlegs yellow to whitish yellow. 
<emphasis box="[1124,1239,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Tergites blackish brown, shiny; tergites much wider than long; length of tergites 3 and 4 subequal; tergite 5 of male partially telescoped into tergite 4, length slightly more than half of tergite 4; sternite 1 smaller than other sternites but not greatly reduced, a narrow, transverse, complete band, anterior margin broadly concave, posterior margin shallowly emarginate; sternite 2 quadrate, slightly wider anteriorly than posteriorly, lateral margins not conspicuously arched, width slightly greater than length; sternites 3 subquadrate, width just slightly greater than length, lateral margins arched; sternite 4 slightly wider than long, posterior margin wider than anterior margin, lateral margins shallowly arched, sternite 5 robustly U-shaped with anterior base longer than depth of posterior concavity (
<figureCitation box="[1270,1356,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 ‒ 14" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1852,1875]" captionTargetBox="[230,1358,198,1832]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[221,1370,193,1838]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 10 ‒ 14. (10 ‒ 12) Mesonotal setation, dorsal view. (10) Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (11) P. anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). (12) P. schwarzi Cresson (Cuba. Cienfuegos: Cayamas (22 ° 14 ' N, 80 ° 48 ' W; 26 m )). Scale bar = 0.5 mm. (13 ‒ 14) Sternites 1 – 5, ventral view. (13) P. acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (14) P. anisotomoides (Karsch) (Brazil. Pernambuco: Camaragibe, Condomínio dos Cedros (07 ° 58.6 ' S, 35 ° 0.3 ' W; 120 m )). Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054070/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia: Epandrium in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[616,697,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1797,1820]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,208,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1776]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (15) Epandrium, cerci, and presurstylus, posterior view. (16) Same, lateral view. (17) Aedeagus, phallapodeme, postsurstylus, pregonite, hypandrium, and subepandrial plate, ventral view. (18) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054072/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) as an inverted U, dorsal arch thinner than extended, lateral arms, arms nearly straight, parallel, widest subventrally, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[949,1037,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1797,1820]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,208,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1776]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (15) Epandrium, cerci, and presurstylus, posterior view. (16) Same, lateral view. (17) Aedeagus, phallapodeme, postsurstylus, pregonite, hypandrium, and subepandrial plate, ventral view. (18) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054072/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) as a tear drop, narrow dorsally, becoming wider ventrally, ventral margin angularly rounded; cercus in posterior view moderately elongate, hemispherical, rounded dorsomedially, medial margin shallowly convex to nearly straight, generally setulose, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[302,386,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1797,1820]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,208,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1776]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (15) Epandrium, cerci, and presurstylus, posterior view. (16) Same, lateral view. (17) Aedeagus, phallapodeme, postsurstylus, pregonite, hypandrium, and subepandrial plate, ventral view. (18) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054072/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) lunate; presurstylus in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[845,928,836,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1797,1820]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,208,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1776]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (15) Epandrium, cerci, and presurstylus, posterior view. (16) Same, lateral view. (17) Aedeagus, phallapodeme, postsurstylus, pregonite, hypandrium, and subepandrial plate, ventral view. (18) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054072/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) elongate, length about twice base, wider at base with medial, blunt projection, projection bearing 4 setulae, thereafter shallow pedunculate along midlength, apical third tapered to acute point, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[767,854,908,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1797,1820]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,208,1763]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[158,1428,193,1776]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 ‒ 18. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (15) Epandrium, cerci, and presurstylus, posterior view. (16) Same, lateral view. (17) Aedeagus, phallapodeme, postsurstylus, pregonite, hypandrium, and subepandrial plate, ventral view. (18) Same, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054072/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) with basal foot, posterior margin conspicuously emarginate, projected posteriorly subapically, apex broadly pointed; postsurstylus in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1332,943,968]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) more or less L-shaped with narrow, shallowly excavate base, extended process much wider than base, spatulate, parallel sided, apex very shallowly arched, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[728,809,1015,1040]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) L-shaped with short arm as a short, digitiform process, long arm shallowly angulate, narrowed basally, apical half bearing short setulae; pregonite in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1428,1052,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
) irregularly quadrate, corners rounded, slightly produced at apical corner, bearing 4 setulae, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1346,1428,1087,1112]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) triangular, base with one angle rounded, the other acutely pointed, apex bearing 4 setulae; aedeagus in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1159,1184]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) robust, longer than wide, pedunculate, lateral margins conspicuously concave, in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1344,1428,1159,1184]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) elongate, slightly wider basally, shallowly pedunculate, apical fourth tapered, apex narrowly rounded; phallapodeme in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[502,586,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) triangular, keel somewhat rounded rectangular, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1344,1428,1231,1256]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) hour-glass shaped, spool-like; subepandrial plate in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[900,984,1268,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) comma-like, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1344,1428,1268,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) transversely band-like, shallowly arched; hypandrium in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[946,1029,1303,1328]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) robust, longer than wide, posterior portion bifurcate, anterior half quadrate, in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[850,939,1340,1365]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1881,1904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1313,186,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[168,1330,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 19 ‒ 29. Structures of the male terminalia of Peltopsilopa acuta n. sp. (Peru. Loreto: Varillal (03 ° 53.3 ' S, 73 ° 21.1 ' W; 130 m )). (19) Aedeagus, ventral view. (20) Phallapodeme, ventral view. (21) Aedeagus and phallapodeme, lateral view. (22) Subepandrial plate, ventral view. (23) Hypandrium, ventral view. (24) Pregonite, ventral view. (25) Hypandrium, lateral view. (26) Postsurstylus, ventral view. (27) Same, lateral view. (28) Subepandrial plate, lateral view. (29) Pregonite, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1054074/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="87">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) U-shaped with base wider and robustly developed, anterior margin broadly rounded, lateral, posterior extensions slightly oriented medially, posterior margin deeply emarginate, emargination bottle-like swollen basally with narrower neck.
</paragraph>
